{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:09:56.264Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"Fix:** Remove `responsive: true` from the WaveSurfer options list.\n\n3. **[Severity: minor]** — **Missing `waveformRenderer.test.ts` from File Scope** (File Scope → New Files). Step 4 explicitly says \"Write tests for waveformRenderer\" and describes specific test cases, but no corresponding test file (`tests/audio-player/waveformRenderer.test.ts`) is listed in the New Files section. **Fix:** Add `tests/audio-player/waveformRenderer.test.ts` to the File Scope new files list.\n\n4. **[Severity: minor]** — **Invalid CSS value: `border-radius: 50`** (Step 5, line 162). CSS `border-radius` requires a unit. `50` without `%` or `px` won't create circular buttons. For round transport buttons, it should","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:09:57.853Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" be `border-radius: 50%`. **Fix:** Change to `border-radius: 50%`.\n\n5. **[Severity: minor]** — **Astro 5 renamed `<ViewTransitions />` to `<ClientRouter />`** (Step 7, line 195). The spec uses `import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions'` and `<ViewTransitions />`. In Astro ","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:09:59.536Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"5, the canonical API is `import { ClientRouter } from 'astro:transitions'` and `<ClientRouter />`. The old name still works as a deprecated alias, but a greenfield Astro 5 project should use the current API to avoid deprecation warnings. **Fix:** Update to use `<ClientRouter />` from `astro:transitions`.\n\n6. **[Severity: minor]** — **Unnecessary `","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:01.540Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"react` → `preact/compat` alias mention** (Step 1, vitest.config.ts). The spec mentions aliasing `react` → `preact/compat` conditionally, but the entire codebase uses Preact directly (not compat mode). This is confusing configuration guidance for something that isn't needed. **Fix:** Remove the compat alias mention and just configure Preact JSX resolution directly (e.g.,","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:03.667Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" using `@preact/preset-vite` or the Vite resolve for Preact).\n\n### Criteria Assessment\n\n- **Mission clarity:** Excellent — single clear goal with explicit boundaries. The \"Do NOT\" section is thorough and prevents scope creep.\n- **Step specificity:** Excellent — every step has concrete checkboxes with verifiable outcomes. Steps are well-sequenced with clear dependency flow (types → store → engine → renderer →","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:06.633Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" UI → events → integration).\n- **File scope accuracy:** Very good — nearly complete. Missing the `waveformRenderer.test.ts` file that Step 4 requires. All other files are correctly identified.\n- **Dependency correctness:** Good overall. The KB-002 dependency is correctly stated with specific file assumptions listed. The `@preact/signals` dependency claim is wrong, and wavesurfer.js v7 has an invalid","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:08.070Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" option, but these are catchable at build time.\n- **Testing requirements:** Strong — requires real automated tests with specific test scenarios (mock-based unit tests for engine/renderer, component rendering tests for UI). Test commands are explicit. The quality gate in Step 8 enforces zero failures.\n- **Documentation completeness:** Complete — \"Must Update\" and \"Check If Affected\" sections are present. JSDoc requirement is explicit","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:09.927Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":".\n- **Sizing & review level:** Appropriate — Size L and Review Level 3 (Full) are correct for a task that introduces Preact framework integration, three third-party libraries, View Transitions persistence, and global state management.\n\n### Suggestions\n\n- **Double-download tradeoff:** Both howler.js and wavesurfer.js download the full audio file independently (howler for playback, wavesurfer for waveform decoding","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:11.384Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"). This means each track is downloaded twice. Consider noting this explicitly in the spec and potentially mentioning that a future optimization could use pre-computed waveform peaks (which the \"Do NOT\" section already says is out of scope). For v1 this is acceptable but worth documenting.\n- **`html5: true` tradeoff:** The spec correctly uses `html5: true` for howler.js (necessary for streaming), but","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:13.989Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" this means the Web Audio API isn't used by howler. Worth a brief note that this trades precise audio scheduling for streaming capability.\n- **`setVolume(0)` for wavesurfer.js muting:** While this works, consider whether wavesurfer v7 offers a more explicit mute API or backend option to prevent audio decoding entirely (only using the waveform extraction). This could reduce the bandwidth impact of the double-download","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:16.214Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":".\n- **Error recovery:** The spec handles `loaderror` by setting state to `'error'` but doesn't specify what the UI should show in the error state or how the user can recover (retry? skip to next?). Consider adding a brief error state rendering note to Step 5.\n- **View Transitions `transition:persist` + `client:load` interaction:** The spec correctly identifies using `client:","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:17.424Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"load` for immediate hydration, but it's worth noting that on subsequent page navigations, the persisted component's event listeners for Astro lifecycle events (e.g., `astro:after-swap`) may need explicit handling to re-attach DOM references that could become stale.","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:17.429Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"review_spec","type":"tool_result","detail":"{\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"APPROVE\"}],\"details\":{}}","agent":"triage"}
