{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:22.842Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"The spec for KB-003 has been written and approved. Here's a summary of what it covers:\n\n**Architecture:** A 3-layer audio system:\n1. **howler.js** (`audioEngine.ts`) — cross-browser playback with MP3/OGG format fallback, `requestAnimationFrame` time tracking\n2. **wavesur","type":"text","agent":"triage"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:25.482Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"fer.js v7** (`waveformRenderer.ts`) — visual-only waveform (muted output, synced to howler's position)\n3. **Preact** (`Player.tsx`) — reactive UI layer as an Astro island using `@preact/signals` for state\n\n**Persistence strategy:** `transition:persist` on the player wrapper in `BaseLayout.astro` keeps the Preact component's DOM alive across","type":"text","agent":"triage"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:26.628Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" View Transitions. The module-level signal store naturally persists since the module is never unloaded.\n\n**Page→player communication:** Custom DOM events (`audio-player:play`, `audio-player:pause`, `audio-player:add`) dispatched via helper functions in `src/scripts/audio-player-events.ts` — zero framework coupling so any future page/component can trigger playback.\n\n**9 steps** covering dependency installation, type/store layer, audio engine,","type":"text","agent":"triage"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T10:10:27.367Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" waveform renderer, Preact UI, event system, Astro layout integration, testing, and documentation — with real Vitest tests for the store, audio engine, and component.","type":"text","agent":"triage"}
