{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:21:45.919Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" the computed guard, but it's a latent foot-gun for callers. Consider clamping: `currentIndex.value = newTracks.length > 0 ? Math.min(startIndex, newTracks.length - 1) : -1;`\n\n### Pattern Violations\n\n- None. The module-level singleton pattern matches the spec's description. Signal naming and export style are consistent throughout.\n\n### Test Gaps\n\n- No test for `setPlaylist","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
