{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:23:25.463Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" after `.mp3`? (e.g., `song.mp3?token=abc`)\n- What if `audioUrl` doesn't end in `.mp3`? (though the Track type says \"MP3 format\")\n- Simple string replace `.mp3` → `.ogg` could match substrings in URLs\n\nHowever, since MP3 is the fallback and always provided, the worst case is OGG URL is wrong and Howler falls back to MP3. This is self-healing.\n\n### `effect()` subscription concern\nThe plan says: \"Subscribe to playlist store: when currentIndex signal changes (via effect() from @preact/signals), call load(currentTrack) and auto-play\"\n\nThis is the most architecturally significant decision in this step. Using `effect()` to react to `currentIndex` changes","type":"thinking","agent":"reviewer"}
