{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:23:52.112Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" be to only replace the final `.mp3` extension (e.g., `url.replace(/\\.mp3(\\?[^#]*)?$/, '.ogg$1')`). The current approach works for the expected URL patterns from R2.\n\n3. **[Severity: minor]** — **`effect()` subscription on `currentIndex` needs null-guard**. The plan says \"when `currentIndex` signal changes, call `load(current","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:23:53.888Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"Track)` and auto-play\" — but `currentTrack` can be `null` (e.g., after `clearPlaylist()` sets `currentIndex` to -1). The effect body must guard against `currentTrack.value === null` before calling `load()`, otherwise `load()` will receive null and either throw or create a Howl with undefined src.\n\n### Suggestions\n\n- **Consider using a module-level approach (not a","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
