{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:48:25.820Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" emit `interaction`. So there's no feedback loop when the RAF sync calls `setProgress` → `ws.seekTo`.\n\n2. **`seekTo` behavior**: When user clicks:\n   - `this.seekTo(relativeX)` is called first\n   - Then `this.emit('interaction', relativeX * this.getDuration())` is emitted\n   \n   So when user clicks, wavesurfer:\n  ","type":"thinking","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T11:48:27.688Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" 1. Seeks its internal media to the clicked position\n   2. Emits `interaction` event\n   \n   The `onSeek` callback in waveformRenderer receives this `newTime` (which is `relativeX * duration`), converts it to a fraction, and the Player component calls `audioEngine.seek(fraction)`. This is correct.\n\n3. **Important: `seekTo`","type":"thinking","agent":"reviewer"}
