{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:03:31.565Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" fine, but note that if future pages use different layouts, the player CSS would need to be imported there too. Alternatively, the import could live in `global.css` or the Player component itself (Astro handles CSS bundling for island components). Not blocking — just something to keep in mind for KB-004 when additional layouts may be introduced.\n\n- **Body padding on non-player pages**: The Player component's `use","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:03:33.510Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"Effect` adds `audio-player-body-padding` class to `document.body`. When the player is in collapsed/idle state, the 80px padding is still applied. This means all pages have unnecessary bottom padding even when the player isn't active. Consider making the padding conditional on the expanded state — but this is a polish item, not a correctness concern.\n\n- **Build verification scope**: The step says \"verify `npm run","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:03:36.274Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" build` succeeds.\" Since the Player uses `wavesurfer.js` and `howler` (browser-only APIs), the SSR build may hit issues if those modules aren't properly handled. The `client:load` directive means the component only runs client-side, so this should be fine — but worth the worker paying attention to any SSR bundling errors during the build step.","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
