{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:07:01.482Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":"the project uses `astro@^5.18.1`), this is aliased to `ClientRouter` and marked as `@deprecated`. It still works, but the canonical Astro 5 API is `ClientRouter`. No functional impact, but downstream linting or future Astro 6 compatibility may flag this.\n\n   **Suggested fix:** Change to `import { ClientRouter } from 'astro:transitions';`","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:07:03.362Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" and use `<ClientRouter />` in the template.\n\n2. **`src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro:25`** minor — The `transition:persist` directive is applied to a wrapper `<div>` around `<Player client:load />`. This is correct and works — Astro will keep this DOM subtree alive across page navigations. However, the `transition:persist` attribute works by preserving the DOM element with that identifier","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:07:05.592Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":". If any other page also renders an element with `transition:persist=\"audio-player\"`, they'll be swapped. With only one layout using this, there's no issue.\n\n3. **`src/components/AudioPlayer/Player.tsx:49-50`** minor (pre-existing from Step 5, not Step 7) — The `useEffect` dependency on `currentTrack.value?.id` uses a derived","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
{"timestamp":"2026-05-19T12:07:08.402Z","taskId":"KB-003","text":" chain that may not trigger re-initialization if a different track has the same id (unlikely but theoretically possible), and the effect won't fire on the first render if `currentTrack` is already set by the time the component mounts (since the dependency value doesn't change). This is fine for the current architecture since the effect also depends on `waveformContainerRef.current` being available.\n\n### Pattern Violations\n- No","type":"text","agent":"reviewer"}
